<plot>Documentary about the colorful life of Vienna-born Adolf Molnar (1905-1988), who served during WWII in Finnish troops. He was born in Fasanviertel, Vienna, and lived a carefree, adventurous life as a sailor, journalist, writer, and wanderer. Molnar escaped Hitler's reign through Europe, before finally settled down in Helsinki after the war. The film is based on his autobiography "Suuri ilveily" (Unstet und fl√ºchtig). The documentary contains archive footage, dramatized sequences and interviews.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?523925</url></doc>
